---
/**
 * watermarks-deep-dive · Figure 5 — Level 5: a window's lifetime (allowed lateness
 * → state GC → side output) plus the completeness/latency/cost trade-off triangle.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/streaming-event-driven/watermarks-deep-dive.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). Lives as an .astro component for the same reason as
 * Fig1: raw inline SVG with kebab-case attributes is unreliable inside MDX. This
 * figure references the #arw and #arwA arrowhead markers (declared once in the
 * source's hidden top-of-body defs); they are inlined here in a local <defs>
 * (verbatim fills) so the figure resolves standalone.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 200"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A timeline showing window-end, then the allowed-lateness horizon during which late firings update the result, then state garbage-collection after which truly-late events go to a side output. Plus a triangle of the three-way trade-off between completeness, latency and cost."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwA"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#7a1f12"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <!-- lifecycle timeline -->
            <line x1="20" y1="56" x2="380" y2="56" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <text
                x="200"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">A WINDOW'S LIFETIME</text
            >
            <line x1="120" y1="44" x2="120" y2="68" stroke="#7a1f12"></line><text
                x="120"
                y="38"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9"
                fill="#7a1f12">W passes end</text
            >
            <line x1="280" y1="44" x2="280" y2="68" stroke="#9a2417"></line><text
                x="280"
                y="38"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9"
                fill="#9a2417">state GC'd</text
            >
            <rect x="120" y="60" width="160" height="20" rx="4" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text x="200" y="74" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#244a2e"
                >allowedLateness → late firings update result</text
            >
            <text x="60" y="74" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">on-time</text>
            <text x="200" y="98" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9a2417"
                >after GC → truly late → side output / dead-letter (never silently)</text
            >
            <line
                x1="280"
                y1="84"
                x2="330"
                y2="96"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-dasharray="3 2"
                marker-end="url(#arwA)"></line>
            <rect x="332" y="88" width="58" height="22" rx="5" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect><text x="361" y="103" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >side out</text
            >
            <!-- trade-off triangle -->
            <text
                x="500"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">THREE DIALS</text
            >
            <polygon
                points="500,40 430,150 570,150"
                fill="#fbfaf2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></polygon>
            <text
                x="500"
                y="34"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">completeness</text
            >
            <text
                x="424"
                y="164"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">latency</text
            >
            <text
                x="576"
                y="164"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#8a5a00">cost</text
            >
            <text x="500" y="118" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >pick two,</text
            >
            <text x="500" y="130" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >pay the third</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        After <code>W</code> passes window-end, state is kept for <code>allowedLateness</code>; late
        events re-fire within it. Past the horizon, state is GC'd and truly-late events route to a
        side output.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
